OL,3,CYoung man with brain tumour vows to
OL,4,Cspend last days making others happy
OL,6,FGeorge said: "They gave me 18 months
OL,7,Fand to anyone that's not news you want
OL,8,Fto hear, it takes you by storm. But
OL,9,Ffor me, I had to stay strong for the
OL,10,Fpeople around me. Because at the end
OL,11,Fof the day, after 18 months, they're
OL,12,Fthe ones who have to deal with it, not
OL,13,Fme."
OL,15,FMost of the tumour, which was the size
OL,16,Fof an orange has been removed, but it
OL,17,Fdamaged an eye, and since then he's
OL,18,Fbeen undergoing gruelling rounds of
OL,19,Fchemo and radiotherapy in Winchester.
